.TH "gpiochip_fwd_create" 9 "gpiochip_fwd_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gpiochip_fwd_create \- Create a new GPIO forwarder
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct gpiochip_fwd *" gpiochip_fwd_create
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int ngpios "  ","
.BI "struct gpio_desc *descs[] "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Parent device pointer
.IP "ngpios" 12
Number of GPIOs in the forwarder.
.IP "descs" 12
Array containing the GPIO descriptors to forward to.
This array must contain \fIngpios\fP entries, and must not be deallocated
before the forwarder has been destroyed again.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function creates a new gpiochip, which forwards all GPIO operations to
the passed GPIO descriptors.
.SH "RETURN"
An opaque object pointer, or an \fBERR_PTR\fP-encoded negative error
code on failure.
